        The powers of a psionicist fall into 2 classes.  The first is
the effects and the second is the modifiers.  The effects comprise about
80% of the 55+ powers and they affect various things on the mud.  They
allow the psionicist to teleport, strike enemies with mental blows,
reduce the weight of objects, see and hear things far away, increase
armor protection, alter their alignment, etc.  The modifiers affect the
other powers.  They allow a psionicist to take a power that he or she
already has and make it better.  Make it do more damage, cost less SP,
take less time to use, or last for a longer duration.
        Each psionicist gets a number of 'psionic potential' points with
each guild level and uses these points to buy new powers.  The powers
cost different amounts of points depending on how powerful they are.
The psionicist is free to buy many cheaper powers, a few expensive ones,
or save the points to get more powers next level.  How a psionicist
spends these points determines what sort of character that psionicist
becomes.
